title: Stanford CS229: Machine Learning Full Course taught by Andrew Ng
description: Led by Andrew Ng, this course provides a broad introduction to machine learning and statistical pattern recognition. Topics include: supervised learning (generative/discriminative learning, parametric/non-parametric learning, neural networks, support vector machines); unsupervised learning (clustering, dimensionality reduction, kernel methods); learning theory (bias/variance tradeoffs, practical advice); reinforcement learning and adaptive control. The course will also discuss recent applications of machine learning, such as to robotic control, data mining, autonomous navigation, bioinformatics, speech recognition, and text and web data processing.

title: AI/ML Tech Series 1 | AI / ML - Know About technology, Before you start
description: Dive into the exciting world of technology with 'Future-Proof Your Knowledge: AI/ML Tech Series 1.' This series is like a fun adventure that helps you understand Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning, two cool technologies that are changing the future. Whether you're just starting or already know a bit, we've got something for everyone. We'll break down the tricky stuff and show you the ropes, making it easy to grasp the ins and outs of AI and ML. This isn't just about today – it's about preparing for what's coming next! So, get ready to boost your tech skills, explore the possibilities, and be a part of the future. Join us in Series 1 and let's make learning tech both exciting and easy!
